*English: [[the]] (1,2,3,4)

===Relative pronoun===
'''der'''

# In a subordinate clause, indicates a person or thing referenced in the main clause.  Used with masculine singular referents.
#: Ich kenne einen Mann, ''der'' dass kann: I know a man ''who'' can do that.

====Translations====
*English: [[who]], [[that]]

